<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Justin_Verlander&amp;action=edit&amp;section=31" title="Edit section: Notes"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="reflist reflist-lower-alpha">
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-Astros_ERA_leader-147"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Astros_ERA_leader_147-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Verlander's 1.75 ERA trailed only <a href="/wiki/Nolan_Ryan" title="Nolan Ryan">Nolan Ryan</a>, who, with a 1.69 ERA, won the  NL ERA title during the strike-shortened <a href="/wiki/1981_Major_League_Baseball_season" title="1981 Major League Baseball season">1981 season</a> for best in club history overall,<sup id="cite_ref-144" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-144">&#91;144&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-145" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-145">&#91;145&#93;</a></sup> and thereby rating as best-ever in an unshortened 162-game season.<sup id="cite_ref-mctaggart100522_146-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mctaggart100522-146">&#91;146&#93;</a></sup> </span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Player_of_the_Week-169"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Player_of_the_Week_169-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Nolan Ryan (13), Roger Clemens (11) and Randy Johnson (10) were the first three pitchers to be named Player of the Week 10 or more times, and each pitched for the Astros.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-ruth-196"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-ruth_196-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Co-winner with teammate <a href="/wiki/Jos%C3%A9_Altuve" title="José Altuve">José Altuve</a>.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
